Why influencer THIGHS never SMOOSH - aaaand let’s talk high heels. 

So heels are used a lot in pics for the obvious things (elongate legs, sassy posture, etc). 

But they also make it easier to balance and pose in certain crouching positions — like this one. 

Here’s how it works:

I’m HIDING my thigh smoosh by tucking my thigh UNDER itself, using my calf to pull my cellulite taunt. 

I arch my back and lift my weight OFF my legs, so I’m not actually crouching. This also prevents thigh smoosh. 

I have a wedgie for longer leg lined. 

I’m not breathing. 

And I’m using my hair to hide my neck skin folds. 

Versus crouching like a normal person (in high heels 😂). Or hey, sitting comfy. 

I love posing. I think it’s fun and fire and here’s to body autonomy ❤️. 

But also just remember this stuff happens ALL THE TIME. 

And your unposed, super comfy self is just as INCREDIBLE AND WORTHY as anything we see online. 

You got this. 

No thigh tucks required. 

❤️🥰❤️

#instavsreality #selflove #bodyconfidence #posingtruths

❤️ To ‘untraditional’ families ❤️ I lived in a commune for a while after my mom died. It drew me in with big promises, low rent and kind people. Yet in many ways, it was awful. 

There were parties. A lot of parties. And substances and sticky stacks of plates, bugs, crumbling walls and corners that folded into mould. After I left, it was torn down, condemned by the city as unsafe. 

I didn’t want to be there. 
I thought I had nowhere else to go. 

Lisa showed me otherwise. 

A scholarship advisor at my university, Lisa had started to step into the hole my mom left with her death.

And one night, when the commune became too much, Lisa insisted I come home. 

‘There’s a spare room. We can decorate it. We can make it feel like you.’

We bought pillows and blankets and she filled the fridge with my favourite foods.

She became family. 
She is still family. 
And I’m thankful every day. 

So here, now, I just wanted to send love to everyone who comes from a background that is a little more ‘unique’. 

Honor your story. 
Be proud of your narrative. 
And lean into the people that help you feel the sun. 

Because houses can be found everywhere,
But families sit inside the soul. And that is a beautiful thing indeed. 

#family #nontraditionalfamily

Let’s sing along to some of the HORRIBLY stupid, SEXIST stuff that’s happened in SPORTS this month - because my gosh, it’s either that or scream. 

In case you’ve missed it, here are the ‘HOW is this still happening in 2021?!!?’ headlines:

Norway volleyball players were fined for wanting to wear shorts on court (instead of the usual bikini bottoms). 

Meanwhile a British para-Olympic athlete was told her shorts were ‘too short’.

Aaaand swimming caps designed for Black hair were banned. The Olympic committee said they didn’t understand why anyone would need them.

I can’t believe we are still here. STILL. 
In a space where women’s bodies are policed by men. 

It’s not police officers on a beach putting a ruler to a woman’s swimsuit. 
But it’s not far off. 

So with this little trendy sea shanty, I hope the more important point comes across:

Enough of this nonsense. 
For the athletes of today,
For the little girls of tomorrow,
Enough. 

#selflove #seashanty #feminism

node.text:
This summer, wear those shorts. Rock that bikini. Jump in the water and don’t be afraid to try something new. Do it for you. And darling, do it for her. 

Because when you live in your truth, you show other women they can do it too. Without shame. Full of joy. Exactly as you exist right now. 

I’ve been thinking about this a lot lately. 
I’ve started learning to dive. 
And friends have been helping me along the way. 

They’re showing me the moves and working on my belly flops. 
But they’re also cheering. 
Clapping. 
Jumping in themselves. 
Trying their own tricks, 
Making their own mistakes, 

Reminding me that it’s ok to stumble, fall, crash and splash.
Reminding me we can laugh and be happy all the same. 

They’ve inspired me. 
And today, today I hope these words help inspire you
To get out there,
Enjoy summer,
And glow like the amazing sun you are.

You never know who might be encouraged by your light.

x

#selflove #bodyconfidence #weartheshorts #bodyacceptance

If you wouldn’t say it to a little girl, don’t say it to yourself. 

Not about your body. 
Not about what you can and cannot eat. 
Not about your soul, your heart, YOU. 

Because like a child, you deserve food. Movement. Health. 
You deserve kindness and softness. 
Love and acceptance. 

You deserve the warmth of knowing you, 
With all your delicate struggles and incredible strengths, 
Are who you’re meant to be. 

x

Kit @womensbest @womensbestwear

node.text:
How many articles have you seen about BEATING HUNGER?

Crushing those cravings?
Skipping that meal?
 
How many ‘tips’ have you read to ‘end that appetite’?

Like chewing gum. 
Going for a walk. 
Drinking water. 
Painting your nails. 
Taking a nap. 

How many times have you been told not to TRUST YOUR BODY but to IGNORE IT, smother it, starve it? 

Too many, is my guess. 
Too many times. 

And so we learn that hunger queues are bad. But calorie free drinks are good. 
Carbs are evil. But processed diet chemicals are ok. 

We stop tuning in to ourselves, 
Because we are so surrounded by the screams of a 70 billion dollar industry. 

So today, I just want to remind you:
It’s ok to be hungry. 
And it’s ok to eat. 
Our bodies are smart, so so smart. 
And when they need fuel, they’re programmed to say so. 

You deserve to fuel yourself. 

Stop obsessing over shrinking. 
You were born to expand. 

x 

Skit IB @eribodysbeautiful 
Final quote IB @meganroselane 

Workout kit @womensbest @womensbestwear 

#selflove #womensbestathlete #bodyconfidence #dietculture #bodyacceptance

Ever wonder how influencers get all those happy candid moments when they’re ALONE? I’ve partnered with @FractureME, my favorite glass photo printing company, to share some fun photo truths. 

But first, a lil’ shoutout to @FractureME, who are the folks behind this idea and all the amazing glass prints here. They’re a carbon-neutral company that makes it really easy to turn memories into elegant wall art. 

Now for the photo truths: 

Lots of influencers use iPhones, tripods and clickers, OR cameras and connected iPhone apps, to take ‘casual, relaxed’ snaps. 

Like for this pic here, I needed the camera to be pretty high, so I balanced a taped up camera on a tripod. I stuck that on a garbage bin. I then put the whole lot onto a suitcase. I used a CLICKER APP connected to my phone to take the pic. Aaaand I took around 30 snaps before I got one where my hand didn’t look a bit wild holding the glass print. 

This sort of stuff happens ALL THE TIME behind the scenes — and that’s OK. 

Today @FractureME and I just want to remind you that all your moments are worthy ones: the unfiltered, the unposed, the curated, the composed. Just make sure you share what makes you feel like you! 

Use Danae20 for 20% off. And if you feel like possibly WINNING USD 500 in @FractureME gift cards, go ahead and share your favourite moments with #SummerUnfiltered.

For all the women who learned all the wrong things about periods, 
About hormones,
About the cycles that happen and surge and swirl throughout the female body.

We are the witches they tried to burn.
The humans they try to shrink.

We are strong, not shameful.
Infinitely powerful, not weak.

And in this, in this, we are together.

node.text:
Trust the timing of your life. Because darling, you are creating your own map — and the path, the path is uniquely yours. 

I am so glad that I didn’t find this route, of forever-love and engagement and marriage, in my 20s, 
I wasn’t ready. 
In my heart, in myself, I wasn’t ready. 

I needed time to grow. 

So I worked on loving my body, 
On recovering from years of disordered eating. 
I experienced heartbreak,
I changed jobs. Made new friends. Tripped. Travelled. 

I learned. 

And in my 30s — the magic number women are taught to fear — I started to love myself. 
My heart. My softness. My strength. 

After 32, I became ready to love someone else too.
Then I found him.

So no, no, I don’t regret that my life has unfolded this way. 
Because we each have our own journeys,
Our own paths. 
And our timelines are as varied as the sands tumbling through a clock: 
Unfurling in unique patterns, 
Creating beautiful, infinitely different designs. 

Today, wherever you are in your journey,
I just want to remind you: 

Don’t be ashamed of the steps that brought you here. 
Don’t doubt the routes that come next. 
You are strong enough to drive at your own speed, 
And brave enough to go amazing places. 

You have this. 
Wherever you are, you have this. 
Because you, my dear, are creating your own map. 
And the path is yours. 

x
